The paper deals with privacy-preserving data analytics, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The framework presented in the paper is designed to work with dynamic user groups, which suggests that it may involve database management (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions that polynomial-based analysis is supported, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
